    "46": {
      "title": "“Gatekeeper”",
      "text": "<p><img src=\"images/029a.jpg\" alt=\"Judea Capta coin, 70&ndash;81 CE. The image symbolizes Rome&rsquo;s suppression of the Jewish uprising: on the left, a victorious Roman soldier; on the right, a desolate woman seated under a palm tree, a personification of captive Judea. \" width=\"400\" height=\"191\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Judea Capta</strong> coin, 70&ndash;81 CE. The image symbolizes Rome&rsquo;s suppression of the Jewish uprising: on the left, a victorious Roman soldier; <br />on the right, a desolate woman seated under a palm tree, a personification of captive Judea.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/029b.jpg\" alt=\"Israel Coins &amp; Medals Corporation, Reverse of Israel Liberata, 1958, the first commemorative medal minted in Israel; a figure from its obverse (the &ldquo;gardener&rdquo;) appears on the far left of the carpet.\" width=\"400\" height=\"396\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Israel Coins &amp; Medals Corporation, <strong>Reverse of Israel Liberata</strong>, 1958, the first commemorative medal minted in Israel; <br />a figure from its obverse <a href=\"#22\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">(the &ldquo;gardener&rdquo;</a>) appears on the far left of the carpet.&nbsp;<br />Photo courtesy of ICMC - Israel Coins &amp; Medals Corporation</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/029c.jpg\" alt=\"Image of a Roman soldier on an American Express card\" width=\"400\" height=\"467\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Image of a Roman soldier on an <strong>American Express</strong> card</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><img src=\"images/029d.jpg\" alt=\"New Israeli Shekel coin, 1986, featuring a lily and the word for &ldquo;Judea&rdquo; in Paleo-Hebrew script\" width=\"400\" height=\"200\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>New Israeli Shekel coin</strong>, 1986, featuring a lily and the word for &ldquo;Judea&rdquo; in Paleo-Hebrew script</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/030a.jpg\" alt=\"Simon de Vos, Repentant Mary Magdalene, 1650\" width=\"400\" height=\"501\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Simon de Vos, <strong>Repentant Mary Magdalene</strong>, 1650</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"images/030b.jpg\" alt=\"Israeli Shekel coin, 1980, featuring Temple chalice. In Christian iconography, the chalice is an attribute of Mary Magdalene.\" width=\"400\" height=\"199\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Israeli Shekel coin</strong>, 1980, featuring the Temple chalice&nbsp;<br />In Christian iconography, the chalice is an attribute of Mary Magdalene.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>"
    },
