    "76": {
      "title": "“The Brain”",
      "text": "<div><img src=\"images/085b.jpg\" alt=\"יצחק דרורי, החשוד המרכזי בשוד הכספות בבנק הפועלים במשפטו, 1985 צילום: יצחק אלהרר &quot;סקופ 80&quot;\" width=\"400\" height=\"606\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"></span></div>\r\n<div align=\"LEFT\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><font size=\"2\"><br />Yitzhak Drori, prime suspect in the </font><font size=\"2\"><b>Bank Hapoalim break-in</b></font><font size=\"2\">, at his trial. Photo: Scoop 80, 1985<br /><br />In his autobiography, Dror wrote the words inscribed in the carpet&rsquo;s border, describing his preparation for breaking into the vault: <strong>&ldquo;I touched every part of my bride [the vault] and lovingly said to her, &lsquo;Now I need to take you apart and study you until I know everything. I will find your weak spots and I will treat you like a queen.&rsquo; I went on caressing her and playing with her locks . . .&rdquo;</strong> (Yitzhak Drori and Ilan Behar, The Brain, Sifriyat Ma&rsquo;ariv, 1988, p. 323; Hebrew).<br /></font></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>"
    },
